{
  "texts": [
    "The EU legislator prescribes risk mitigation measures proportionate to the risk magnitude.",
    "As a result, risk management measures are allocated according to the four risk categories of the AIA.",
    "Hence, the risk considered in the AIA is legal in nature, expressing the potential detriment that comes from the violation of a legal norm by an AIs (i.e., principles and rules) (Mahler, 2007).",
    "24 However, the AIA's risk assessment model does not fulfil the distinctive nature of the legal risk as it does not evaluate comparatively and proportionately the specific weight of legal norms.",
    "Quite the opposite, risk assessment in the AIA seems modelled as a neutral tool that treats legal norms as technical standards which are either met or not (Smuha et al., 2021)."
  ]
}